			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<a href="http://www.themadvideo.com" target="_blank"><img src="http://blog.themadvideo.com/wp-content/uploads/TMV-background.png" style="width: 100%;" /></a></p>
<p>
<strong>The Company</strong></p>
<p>
The Mad Video is an online platform that allows anyone to add tags and interactivity to online videos. &nbsp;You may now tag valuable information embedded within videos -- from products to locations to people -- with just one click, and find new ways to inform and interact with viewers.</p>
<p>
The company, originating in Madrid and based in San Francisco, was also recently announced winners for <a href="http://thestartupconference.com/startup-competition/">Best Startup at the 2013 Startup Conference</a>, and <a href="http://tech.co/the-mad-video-wins-san-franciscos-hottest-showcasing-startup-2013-05">San Francisco&rsquo;s Hottest Showcasing Startup</a> at Tech Cocktail.</p>
<p>
<strong>The Role</strong></p>
<p>
This role will help support the marketing and operations team with new business opportunities and communications. &nbsp;You&rsquo;ll be working intimately with our founders and management team on researching new priorities, organizing collateral, executing on actions and measuring progress. &nbsp;This is a full time paid internship in our Madrid office.</p>
<p>
We are looking for candidates who are self-starters, learn quickly and are passionate about entrepreneurship and technology. &nbsp;We like simplicity, common sense and initiative. &nbsp;This role may also lead into a permanent position within the company.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Researching and drafting material / demos for prospective clients</li>
<li>
Help manage and update online marketing campaigns</li>
<li>
Build reports and outlines for internal analysis</li>
<li>
Follow up on customer service issues</li>
<li>
Help test new products and features in our platform</li>
<li>
Provide administrative support to the team</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Qualifications</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Bachelors Degree (or equivalent) in Business, Marketing, Computer Science / Engineering, Telecommunications or related</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Must Haves</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Goal orientated, ability to prioritize multiple tasks and stick to deadlines</li>
<li>
Proficient researcher, knows about resources and tools on the Internet</li>
<li>
Familiarity with e-commerce, online marketing disciplines and analytics platforms</li>
<li>
Experience with best practices in social media</li>
<li>
Excellent communication skills and ability to work in teams</li>
<li>
Fluency in English - our team speaks and writes in English all day</li>
</ul>
<p>
Please note that all applicants <u>must submit material in English</u> in order to be considered for this internship.</p>
